</s>
</head>
<p>
<s>
<hi rend="bold">
Arabic
</hi>
</s>
<s>
(
العَرَبِيَّة‎
)
is
a
group
of
Semitic
dialects
spoken
by
more
than
420
million
people
,
mainly
in
<ref target="North%20Africa">
North
Africa
</ref>
and
the
<ref target="Middle%20East">
Middle
East
</ref>
.
</s>
<s>
The
literary
form
(
Modern
Standard
Arabic
,
MSA
)
is
the
liturgical
language
for
1.6
billion
<ref target="Muslims">
Muslims
</ref>
and
is
the
official
written
form
of
the
language
.
</s>
</p>
<p>
<s>
For
communication
purposes
while
traveling
and
using
this
guide
,
it
is
very
important
to
note
the
differences
between
MSA
and
dialects
since
they
are
largely
mutually
unintelligible
.
</s>
<s>
Well-educated
people
will
generally
be
able
to
understand
MSA
,
but
usually
respond
in
their
local
dialects
.
</s>
<s>
Comprehension
of
dialects
between
different
regions
will
drop
significantly
.
</s>
<s>
It
is
therefore
recommended
that
travelers
focus
on
learning
the
relevant
dialect
for
their
destination
for
spoken
communication
,
while
using
MSA
as
a
written
reference
.
</s>
</p>
<head>
<s>
Pronunciation
guide
</s>
</head>
